news.title: Norway government calls off plan to sell land in Svalbard
news.para: The archipelago is located halfway between mainland Norway and the North Pole, in an Arctic region that has become a geopolitical and economic hotspot as the ice melts and relations grow ever frostier between Russia and the West.

news.title: Home prices in Australia rise by 0.7% in June 2024
news.para: Data from CoreLogic showed national home prices climbed 0.7% in June from May when it gained 0.8%. Prices are up 8.0% on a year earlier.

news.title: New home prices in China rise by 0.15% in June 2024
news.para: The average price for new homes across 100 cities edged up 0.15% month-on-month in June, weaker than a 0.25% gain in May, according to data from property researcher China Index Academy.

news.title: Land prices in Japan rise by 2.3% in 2023
news.para: Average land prices climbed 2.3% last year, rising for the third straight year, a National Tax Agency survey showed, extending gains from a 1.5% increase in 2022 and a 0.5% rise in 2021.

news.title: Government must rejig housing pension product for silver economy
news.para: The representation of seniors in India will double from 10% today to over 20% in 2050, and the count will be well above 350 million. According to an Agewell Foundation Survey (2023), only 26% of Indian seniors reported themselves to be in a good financial status.

news.title: House prices in UK rise by 0.2% in June 2024: Nationwide
news.para: Britain's housing market boomed during the coronavirus pandemic but it has slowed after the Bank of England pushed interest rates to their highest since 2008 last year.

news.title: India's elevator business is undergoing a major transformation
news.para: The traditional approach to elevator maintenance involved technicians attending to malfunctions only after they occurred. This disruptive and protracted downtime strategy may harm property operations and tenants' experiences.

news.title: Blueprint for change: Navigating India's green building frontier
news.para: India's commitment to addressing climate change is evident through its ambitious renewable energy targets and a formidable mission to achieve net zero by 2070, and efforts are being made in every conceivable direction to achieve this.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires seven acres land in Bengaluru
news.para: residential project, having a developable potential of approximately nine lakh sq ft with an estimated revenue potential of about Rs 1,200 crore.

news.title: BAF and RERI sign MoU to spread awareness amongst homebuyers in Bengaluru
news.para: This partnership aims to benefit nearly 1,300 apartment and villa resident welfare associations (RWAs), representing almost 300,000 households and approximately one and a half million citizens.

news.title: Delhi metro looks to open three phase-IV corridors by 2026
news.para: Delhi Metro Rail Corporation (DMRC) officials said the Phase 4 expansion project is progressing rapidly with a target of opening all three priority corridors comprising 65 kilometres of new lines by 2026.

news.title: Kenya faces affordable housing shortage amidst growing urban population
news.para: The government plans to build 250,000 houses each year, aimed at eventually closing a housing deficit that World Bank data puts at 2 million units. The plan was launched in 2022, but no data is available on the number of houses already completed.

news.title: Telangana CM asks officials to prepare Warrangal's master plan 2050
news.para: The chief minister suggested to them developing the proposed Outer Ring Road in such a way to connect one national highway with another in the city.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai rise by 12% in June 2024: Report
news.para: The figure is expected to reach around 11,600 units this month, the bulk of the registration is of housing properties, Strong buyer confidence in Mumbai has kept property sales above the 10,000 mark in each of the six months of 2024 calendar year.

news.title: Rajasthan government forms new committee to probe single lease cases
news.para: It is noteworthy that during the tenure of the previous government, a committee was constituted to withdraw the case from the court on the irregularities in the single lease case.

news.title: Sweden's SBB creditors exchange debt for residential bonds in $158 million swap
news.para: SBB is at the centre of a Swedish property market bubble that began to unravel in 2022 when inflation and interest rates soared, triggering sharp cuts to its credit ratings and a plunge in its share price.

news.title: Government to reconstruct 28,643 dilapidated flats: Tamil Nadu CM
news.para: The Board currently maintains 1.94 lakh flats across Tamil Nadu and among them, 28,643 dwellings have been found to be dilapidated, the chief minister said.
